In Valenica -- Yuso was our favorite Paella, 2DayLanguages our favorite language school and visit Gulliver (especially if you have kids). Things you need to know about the apartment: This is a six story walkup. The preschool in the courtyard can be loud for 2 hours in mid afternoon during the week. You will not sleep during Fallas (March) because you are 1/2 block away from one of the greatest events on planet earth, but it's loud and goes on until 3am.  The air conditioner/heater works great, but you have to close the door to the room you want to heat or cool (we tried heating the whole place, but it's too big). The television is an ornament (no antenna, no cable). Triple clip your clothing on the drying line because it can get windy up there. All minor things that should not keep you from staying in this wonderful spot! Thank you Macarena, you are AWESOME!

# baños --> imputar con la mediana del barrio donde esta
list_limpiado_pisos <- list_limpiado_pisos %>%
  group_by(neighbourhood_cleansed) %>%
  mutate(bathrooms = ifelse(is.na(bathrooms),
                            median(bathrooms, na.rm = TRUE),
                            bathrooms)) %>%
  ungroup()

# habitaciones --> imputar con la mediana del barrio donde esta
list_limpiado_pisos <- list_limpiado_pisos %>%
  group_by(neighbourhood_cleansed) %>%
  mutate(bedrooms = ifelse(is.na(bedrooms),
                            median(bedrooms, na.rm = TRUE),
                            bedrooms)) %>%
